class Laptops {
     String name;
     int price;
     int quantity;
     
     public Laptops(String name,int price,int quantity){
         this.name = name;
         this.price = price;
         this.quantity = quantity;
     }
     
     public int revenue(){
         return quantity*price;
     }
     
     public void display(){
         System.out.println("Laptops name is: "+ name);
         System.out.println("Laptops price is: "+ price);
         System.out.println("Quantity of laptops: "+ quantity);
         System.out.println("Total cost: "+ revenue());
     }
}
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Laptops b = new Laptops("Dell",54000,2);
        
        b.display();
       
        
    }
}


Explanation:
Defining a class and creating an object.
Using constructors to initialize object properties.
Implementing methods for functionality (like revenue calculation).
Printing the results and displaying data on the console.
